OL,4,Cmaternity cover and 'grandparent leave'
OL,6,FShe adds, "If you are a child with
OL,7,Fjust one parent, you're not getting
OL,8,Fequitable access to time with a parent
OL,9,Fthat a child with two parents is
OL,10,Fcurrently getting."
OL,12,FShe explains the early years gap is
OL,13,Falso felt more greatly by parents on a
OL,14,Flower-income, because "they simply
OL,15,Fcannot afford any more time off work
OL,16,Fbeyond their six weeks, so some
OL,17,Fchildren are really missing out at the
OL,18,Fmoment".
OL,20,FVanessa Carre gave up work to care for
OL,21,Fher granddaughter, Betty.
